text.paragraph:
The use of doxepin hydrochloride on a once-a-day dosage regimen in geriatric patients should be adjusted carefully based on the patient's condition (see 
                              PRECAUTIONS - Geriatric Use
                           ).

Sedating drugs may cause confusion and oversedation in the elderly; elderly patients generally should be started on low doses of doxepin hydrochloride and observed closely. (See 
                              PRECAUTIONS - Geriatric Use.
                           )
